s also observed by LAMOST,\nthe LAMOST Teff values are cooler than the KIC Teff by several hundred K, and\nwould move these stars out of the instability regions. It is possible that a\nmore accurate determination of their Teff and log g would move some of the\nother `constant' stars out of the instability regions. However, if average\n(random) errors in Teff are taken into account, 15 to 52 stars may still\npersist within the instability regions. Explanations for these `constant'\nstars, both theoretical and observational, remain to be investigated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 31 Jan 2015 22:59:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-03"}
