c, the semi-major axis is\nestimated to be ~10^{-2} pc for 10^7 Msun black hole with typical orbital and\ndisk parameters. We also briefly discuss the possibility that central objects\nof observed warped maser disks in active galactic nuclei are supermassive black\nhole binaries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 1 Feb 2015 00:47:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-15"}
